Make sure to have the Expo Go app installed in your device and run the following command:
`npx expo start -c`
Connect your device via USB cable on windows PC



app structure
task-management-app/
├── src/
│   ├── components/       # For reusable components
│   │   └── ExampleComponent.tsx
│   ├── screens/          # For different screens of the app
│   │   └── HomeScreen.tsx
│   ├── styles/           # Centralized styles
│   │   └── globalStyles.ts
│   ├── assets/           # Images, fonts, etc.
│   ├── hooks/            # Custom hooks (if any)
│   ├── App.tsx           # Main App entry
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json         # TypeScript configuration
├── .eslintrc.js          # Linting config (optional)
└── babel.config.js
